---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="ICP & ABM Targets" section="icp">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">05 · ICP & ABM</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Who to target, <em>who to enrich, what to send.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Top-10 DSO status, top 11-30 emerging targets, decision-maker map. Aspen is ALREADY a Clerri customer (Membersy-administered) — the real top-10 displacement targets are Heartland, PDS Health, Smile Brands.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Aspen is already a customer — stop targeting them. The real displacement targets are Heartland, PDS Health, and Smile Brands. Enrich the top 30, personalize the outreach.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="icp"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="icp">0 / 0</span> ABM tasks completed</p>

  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">Research correction — read first</div>
    <p>The original brief listed Aspen Dental as a "missing top-10 target." This is wrong. <strong>Aspen Dental Savings Plan ($49/yr) is administered by Membersy LLC (now Clerri)</strong> per Aspen's own T&C PDF. Clerri renewed the partnership in 2024. Aspen is an <strong>expansion target, not a new logo</strong>. The real top-10 displacement targets are Heartland, PDS Health, and Smile Brands.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- TOP 10 -->
  <h2>Top 10 US DSOs — status &amp; ABM read</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Clerri claims 7 of top 10. The conquest targets are <strong>Heartland (uses Coast Dental's Vantage One — displacement-ready) and PDS Health (no public proprietary plan — greenfield)</strong>. Smile Brands runs OneSmile (proprietary) — defended but new CMO Laura Rod is the warm-intro vector.</p>

  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>#</th><th>DSO</th><th>Practices</th><th>Membership Status</th><th>Decision-Maker</th><th>ABM Priority</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>01</td><td><strong>Heartland Dental</strong> (Effingham IL)</td><td>1,800+</td><td>White-labels Coast Dental's Vantage One ($48-96/yr)</td><td>CEO Pat Bauer · <strong>CMO Sherianne James (NEW 2025, ex-CPG/optical)</strong></td><td><span class="pill pill-rose">PRIMARY</span></td></tr>
        <tr style="background:var(--scrub)"><td>02</td><td><strong>Aspen Group</strong></td><td>1,300+</td><td><strong>EXISTING CLERRI/MEMBERSY CUSTOMER</strong> — renewed 2024</td><td>Account team handles</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">EXPANSION</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>03</td><td><strong>PDS Health</strong> (Irvine CA)</td><td>1,100+</td><td>No public proprietary plan — greenfield</td><td>Founder/CEO Stephen E. Thorne IV</td><td><span class="pill pill-rose">PRIMARY</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>04</td><td><strong>MB2 Dental</strong> (Carrollton TX)</td><td>800+</td><td>Within Clerri footprint (DPO model)</td><td>Account team handles</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">EXPANSION</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>05</td><td><strong>Smile Brands</strong> (Irvine CA)</td><td>600+</td><td>Founder Steve Bilt runs OneSmile (proprietary 2015)</td><td>CEO Steve Bilt · <strong>SVP Marketing Laura Rod (NEW 2025)</strong></td><td><span class="pill pill-rose">PRIMARY</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>06</td><td><strong>Sonrava Health</strong></td><td>~600</td><td>Within footprint</td><td>Account team</td><td><span class="pill pill-mint">EXPANSION</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>07</td><td><strong>Smile Doctors</strong> (Brentwood TN)</td><td>580+</td><td>Ortho-focused — different ICP economics</td><td>CMSO Jonathan Kaufman</td><td><span class="pill pill-grey">LOW</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>08</td><td><strong>Affordable Care</strong> (Morrisville NC)</td><td>450+</td><td>Denture/implant-focused, no membership disclosed</td><td>Research needed</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">SECONDARY</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>09</td><td><strong>Western Dental</strong> (Orange CA)</td><td>300+</td><td>Sells Western Dental Plan (insurance, not membership)</td><td>Research needed</td><td><span class="pill pill-grey">LOW</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td><td><strong>Dental Care Alliance</strong> (Sarasota FL)</td><td>350+</td><td>New CCO Trey Mueller DMD · <strong>NEW VP Payor Ops Roma Virani (2025)</strong></td><td>VP Payor Ops Virani — literal title-fit</td><td><span class="pill pill-rose">PRIMARY</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3>Top-10 displacement tasks</h3>
  <div data-section="icp">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-01-heartland-warm" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Heartland: Warm-intro Sherianne James (new CMO, CPG background)</div><div class="task-meta">Via Charlesbank portfolio connections OR ADSO Summit 2026 introduction. CPG background = data-driven, lead with ROI math.</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-02-pds-thorne" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">PDS Health: Cold ABM via PDS Health Foundation board adjacency</div><div class="task-meta">Angle = integrated whole-person care + membership as patient retention layer (PDS rebranded 2024 to medical-dental integrated)</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-03-smile-brands" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Smile Brands: Engage Laura Rod (new SVP Marketing)</div><div class="task-meta">OneSmile is competitive — defended position, but a new SVP Marketing in seat = window. Bain has sponsored Smile Brands events; mutual connection vector.</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-04-dca-virani" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Dental Care Alliance: Direct outreach to Roma Virani (new VP Payor Ops)</div><div class="task-meta">VP Payor Operations is the literal title to pitch membership as PPO alternative. Title-fit is a marketer's dream — write the email today.</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-05-aspen-expansion" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Aspen Group: Expansion plan with account team — what additional features/locations?</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Top-10 DSO intel notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="icp-top10" placeholder="Warm intros identified, conference touchpoints, mutual connections, recent news per target..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <!-- TOP 11-30 EMERGING -->
  <h2>Top 11-30 emerging / mid-market DSOs</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Pulled from Group Dentistry Now "Emerging Dental Groups to Watch" and Becker's tracking. Mid-market sweet spot — large enough to need infrastructure, fast-moving enough to actually decide.</p>

  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead><tr><th>DSO</th><th>Offices</th><th>Why notable</th><th>Approach vector</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>The Smilist</strong> (Great Neck NY)</td><td>100+</td><td><strong>$285M unitranche debt facility 2025</strong> — buying spree</td><td>Capital-fresh, growth pressure — perfect timing for infrastructure pitch</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>SALT Dental Partners</strong> (Phoenix)</td><td>150+</td><td>300% growth in 2 yrs, 20 states, multispecialty</td><td>Hot growth, likely shopping infrastructure — outbound + DEO conference</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Dental365</strong> (New Hyde Park NY)</td><td>100+, 7 states</td><td>Northeast density</td><td>GNYDM trade show capture (Nov 29-Dec 1)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Sage Dental</strong></td><td>130+, FL/GA/TN</td><td>Southeast density</td><td>Hinman Dental Meeting capture (Mar 12-14 Atlanta)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>ProSmile</strong> (PG+Allied merger)</td><td>Recent merger</td><td><strong>New CEO Hugh Carey II</strong> — tech eval window</td><td>Reach out 90-180 days into Carey's tenure</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Risas Dental and Braces</strong></td><td>~40+, Southwest</td><td>Hispanic-market focused</td><td>Bilingual membership pitch — differentiated angle</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Mortenson Dental Partners</strong> (Louisville)</td><td>~125</td><td>Dentist-owned (1979 founded)</td><td>Owner-pride pitch via DEO community</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Smile Obsession</strong> (Chicago)</td><td>17, 35 dentists</td><td>Regional growth</td><td>Qualifying lead, mid-market sweet spot</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Accelerate Dental</strong></td><td>30, West Coast</td><td>Active expansion</td><td>Outbound + Chicago Midwinter touchpoint</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Great Expressions</strong> (Bloomfield Hills MI)</td><td>240+</td><td><strong>New CGO Theresa Neuhauser (2025)</strong></td><td>Pitch as growth lever — CGO is the buying title</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>North American Dental Group</strong> (New Kensington PA)</td><td>240+</td><td>VP Clinical Ops Ray Scott DDS (2025)</td><td>Standard outbound sequence</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Specialized Dental Partners</strong></td><td>250+</td><td>Within Clerri footprint already</td><td>Expansion play</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div data-section="icp">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-06-smilist-outreach" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">The Smilist: Cold outreach within 30 days — $285M debt facility = active growth window</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-07-salt-deo" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">SALT Dental: Get face-to-face at DEO Operations Intensive 2026 (Dallas)</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-08-prosmile-watch" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">ProSmile: 90-180 day watch on new CEO Hugh Carey II — strike when settled</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-09-emerging-list" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Pull Becker's "Emerging Dental Groups" list quarterly into HubSpot for sequenced ABM</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <!-- HIGH-GROWTH GROUP PRACTICES -->
  <h2>High-growth group practices <em>(5-25 locations)</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Below the DSO line but above the solo line. Often the highest-ROI segment — large enough to need real infrastructure, owner-led so faster decisions, less crowded with vendor relationships.</p>

  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Source signal</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Group Dentistry Now <strong>"Emerging Dental Groups to Watch"</strong> annual list. Becker's emerging groups coverage. ADSO new-member announcements.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Buyer titles</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">Owner-Dentist (often clinical lead), Director of Operations, Practice Administrator, sometimes outside COO/CFO from PE-backed groups.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Best channels</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem">DEO Operations Intensive, AADOM podcast circuit, GDN podcast appearances, LinkedIn ABM, regional dental association sponsorships.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ENRICHMENT STACK -->
  <h2>ABM enrichment stack — <em>build the target list.</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Layer 1 — Account list source</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Becker's DSO + DPMS database (manual pull quarterly)</li>
        <li>Group Dentistry Now Emerging Groups list</li>
        <li>Clay (clay.com) — Launch $185/mo for waterfall enrichment</li>
        <li>ZoomInfo / Apollo as secondary verification</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Layer 2 — Decision-maker enrichment</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>LinkedIn Sales Navigator searches by title + company</li>
        <li>Apollo for email + direct dial (210M contact DB)</li>
        <li>Crunchbase/Pitchbook for funding events (triggers)</li>
        <li>Common Room / Default for intent signals (free tier available)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Layer 3 — Activation</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>LinkedIn ABM matched-audience upload (named accounts)</li>
        <li>6sense/Demandbase alternative: signal-based outbound via Common Room</li>
        <li>Personalized AI-generated outbound via Claude API + n8n</li>
        <li>Sales SDR sequence in Apollo / Salesloft</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Layer 4 — Tracking</h4>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>Salesforce account list with custom fields (target tier, membership status, last touch)</li>
        <li>Pardot list segmentation tied to ABM tier</li>
        <li>Quarterly review with Sales on engagement velocity</li>
        <li>Pipeline coverage ratio by ABM tier</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div data-section="icp">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-10-clay-setup" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Set up Clay account ($185/mo) — build the top-100 DSO + 200 emerging-group enrichment list</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-11-sf-segments" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Salesforce account segmentation: Tier 1 (Top 30 DSO), Tier 2 (Emerging 31-100), Tier 3 (Mid-market groups)</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="icp-12-linkedin-matched" data-section="icp" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Upload Tier 1+2 to LinkedIn Matched Audiences for named-account campaigns</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">ABM enrichment notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="icp-enrichment" placeholder="Tool decisions, data quality issues, enrichment win rate, hot accounts identified..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/ad-spend"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">04 · Ad Spend Tiers</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/ad-strategy"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">06 · Ad Creative & Targeting</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
